  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Conversions between Core Graphics-backed images and vImage buffers require that you define the Core Graphics image format. The format describes the number of color channels and how they're ordered; the size, in bits, of the color channels; and whether the image data is premultiplied by an alpha value."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can initialize a Core Graphics image format in either of two ways: by hard-coding values or by deriving the format properties from a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgimageref"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instance. "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Initialize a Core Graphics Image Format from Hard-Coded Values",
          "anchor": "2943381"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The following example shows how you create a Core Graphics image format that describes an image containing four 8-bit channels in the following order: alpha (transparency), red, green, and blue. This combination of properties is referred to as ARGB8888."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/vimage_cgimageformat"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " structure created by this code is reusable. You declare it as a variable because it's passed to subsequent vImage functions as an in-out parameter."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "var format = vImage_CGImageFormat(",
            "    bitsPerComponent: 8,",
            "    bitsPerPixel: 32,",
            "    colorSpace: CGColorSpaceCreateDeviceRGB(),",
            "    bitmapInfo: CGBitmapInfo(rawValue: CGImageAlphaInfo.first.rawValue),",
            "    renderingIntent: .defaultIntent)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2943382",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Initialize a Core Graphics Image Format from an Image",
          "anchor": "2943400"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can derive the properties of a Core Graphics image format from the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgimageref"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instance itself. The following example shows how to create a format description based on the properties of a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiimage"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instance named "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "sourceImage"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ":"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "guard",
            "    let cgImage = sourceImage.cgImage,",
            "    let format = vImage_CGImageFormat(cgImage: cgImage) else {",
            "        return nil",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2943403",
            "title": "Listing 2"
          }
        },
